  "prompt": "When should we change dusk brakes?",
  "response": "You should change dusk brakes (I assume you mean \"disc\" brakes) under the following circumstances:\n\n1. Brake pad wear\n- When brake pad thickness is less than 3-4 mm\n- When brake pad wear indicator makes noise\n- Visible significant wear on brake pads\n\n2. Performance indicators\n- Reduced braking efficiency\n- Squealing or grinding noise when braking\n- Vibration or pulsation in brake pedal\n- Vehicle pulling to one side during braking\n\n3. Mileage recommendations\n- Typically between 30,000-70,000 miles, depending on driving conditions\n- Follow manufacturer's specific recommendations\n\n4. Visual inspection signs\n- Visible damage to brake rotor\n- Uneven brake pad wear\n- Rust or corrosion on brake components\n\n5. Time-based considerations\n- Every 2-3 years, even with low mileage\n- More frequent in harsh driving conditions (city driving, mountainous terrain)\n\nRegular brake maintenance and professional inspection can help determine the right time to change brake components. Always consult your vehicle's manual and a qualified mechanic for specific guidance.",
